Commentary Text: Rashid Khan to Uthappa, out Lbw!! Big shout for lbw, up goes the dreaded finger and Uthappa decides to challenge the call. It's a fair delivery. Don't think there was any bat there. The same has been confirmed by UltraEdge. Three reds on HawkEye and Uthappa has walk back to the dressing room. RR also lose their only review. It's the flat leggie from over the wicket, Uthappa rocks back to work it into the leg-side and plays all around it. It pitched around middle, struck him on the front pad adjacent to the leg-stump. Ball-tracking showed it to be crashing into leg. The partnership has been broken immediately after the time-out. Uthappa lbw b Rashid Khan 18(15) [4s-1 6s-1]

Commentary Text: Khaleel Ahmed to Buttler, out Caught by Bairstow!! Another one bites the dust! RR have lost their three overseas batters inside five overs. SRH are cock-a-hoop and why not! Change of pace from Khaleel Ahmed. Rolled his fingers over the seam and bowled it into the pitch on a short of length. Buttler is a bit early to close his bat-face and gets a faint inside edge. The ball goes over the sticks and dies as it approaches the keeper. Bairstow takes a sharp catch bending forward and tumbling to his left. 26/3 and RR are in deep trouble.. Buttler c Bairstow b Khaleel Ahmed 16(13) [4s-1 6s-1]

Commentary Text: T Natarajan to Buttler, out Smith Run Out!! 1 run completed. This is a big blow for the Royals! Even a dive can't save their skipper. Buttler pulls this shortish ball through square leg and the batters decide to come back for the second, it was Buttler's call. A slight hesitation and Smith eventually obliged. Vijay Shankar, ran to his left from deep backward square leg, picked the ball and fired a decent throw towards the bowler. Natarajan took off the bails to catch Smith short of his crease. Smith didn't have to wait for the third umpire's call. Smith run out (Shankar/T Natarajan) 5(6)
